snippet.textDisplay: Nose bonk crash diagNOSEd. When your front tire cleared the lip, the compressed forks unloaded and extended lower than needed to clear the tree. You usually don't nose bonk something so close to the lip, so you didn't take that extension into account. Plus, the tree is a much smaller radius than you are use to bonking, so the margin for error is much less to ensure you ride away. Watch it in slowmo, pretty easy to see. Glad you are ok. But you gotta start taking better care of your body, man. Peace.
